@Francis I agree with a lot of this, but I'd add that I don't think you need to be a constructor to appreciate the work involved. It's my appreciation that keeps me from seriously attempting it, to be honest!

Of course there's two related skills, filling the board and cluing the answers - just because I rush through a Monday's doesn't mean that I'm not sometimes impressed by a particular bit of clockwork.

If you've not already familiar with Leonard Dawe, his story (too long to reproduce here - too good to précis) is an excellent example of the dangers of unyoking the two skills too far!

