@Charles Engelke

Like @Paul and @Steven L said, this is the kind of clue that runs rampant in late week puzzles--ones that use a lot of ambiguities of language.  For example, semicircle:  Is that a circle that would be perfectly round, but there's segment missing?  Or is it a circle that is complete, but not perfectly round?  We generally assume the first, but the second is equally valid, I've decided.

Crossword clueing relies quite heavily on these often ignored language ambiguities.  I don't know, but I strongly suspect the very high level of punning that goes on in this forum (looking at you, Mike) is an example that the people here recognize and love those linguistic weak spots.

